<tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15401</anchor> <rss>jms-00DB.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00DB</addr>  <route>jms-00DB.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Converting between <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">weak algebra</link> and <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphisms</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>15402</anchor> <rss>jms-00CR.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-00CR</addr>  <route>jms-00CR.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>1</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Lifting <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">homomorphisms</link> to the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link></title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T}   \equiv { \left ( T , \eta , \mu \right )}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> and let <tex>I</tex> be an invertible <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad"><em>weak</em> algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>; let <tex>X</tex> be an arbitrary <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link>. Then a homomorphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot X }</tex> also tracks a <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>, where <tex>\bar { I }</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> of <tex>I</tex> and <tex>s \cdot X</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link> of <tex>X</tex>.</p>      <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline>   We have <link href="jms-00CK.xml" type="local" title="Lifting homomorphisms to the induced monad algebra">already seen</link> that <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot X }</tex> tracks an <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>. It remains to show that this homomorphism preserves the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">successor operation</link>.
  <ol>    <li>      We first unfold the successor operation of the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> on <tex>I</tex>.
            <center><img src="resources/08e01bb878069433ab1603452a169e53-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    <li>      Then we use the algebra property of <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot X }</tex>.
            <center><img src="resources/8d495a60afa31fc515acc16c642b91b9-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    <li>      Then we unfold the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">restricted algebra structure</link>.
            <center><img src="resources/d4fa8dda06f6e72bdae01d93d838d825-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    <li>      Finally we the unitality of the <link href="jms-00C5.xml" type="local" title="Algebra for a monad">monad algebra</link> <tex>X</tex>.
            <center><img src="resources/545052e013d2010ed04e115d6040d267-web.svg"/></center>      </li>  </ol></block>  </mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>2</crumb></trail> <anchor>15403</anchor> <rss>jms-00D9.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-00D9</addr>  <route>jms-00D9.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra</link> homomorphisms to <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">weak algebra</link> <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">homomorphisms</link></title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T}   \equiv { \left ( T , \eta , \mu \right )}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> and let <tex>I</tex> be an invertible <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad"><em>weak</em> algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>; let <tex>X</tex> be an arbitrary <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link>. Then a <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex> also tracks a weak algebra homomorphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot  X }</tex>,  where <tex>\bar { I }</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> of <tex>I</tex> and <tex>s \cdot X</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link> of <tex>X</tex>.</p>      <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline>   <p>We work backwards.</p>  
  <ol>    <li>      First, we unfold the algebra structure of the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/25592c6fd1f2acc7d770d5c48083670b-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      We then use the <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> property of <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/cf12478293987bbed0635893d2e8717a-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      Next we use the <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">algebra homomorphism</link> property of <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/082898a5a8137cff0feb92ca3ea66672-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      We unfold the definition of the <link href="jms-00CD.xml" type="local" title="The induced monad algebra">induced monad algebra</link>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/720475cdd734f6e2f9b1bec2d80213a6-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      We unfold the successor map on the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/bb321a71fafde4d34d348d95da891553-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      We contract the composition of the initial (weak) algebra map with its inverse.
      
            <center><img src="resources/e07aa0172192318fc15eee56518ccae3-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      Finally, we use the unit law of the monad <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/28c7265e93ee4db2d8e73b8fd06918da-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
  </ol></block>  </mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>3</crumb></trail> <anchor>15404</anchor> <rss>jms-00DA.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>jms-00DA</addr>  <route>jms-00DA.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Weak algebra <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">homomorphisms</link> and <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphisms</link> are interchangeable</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> and let <tex>I</tex> be an invertible <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad"><em>weak</em> algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>; let <tex>X</tex> be an arbitrary <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link>. Then a morphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex> in <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> tracks a weak algebra homomorphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot  X }</tex> if and only if it tracks a <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>, where <tex>\bar { I }</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> of <tex>I</tex> and <tex>s \cdot X</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link> of <tex>X</tex>.</p>      <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline>   <p>This follows from the following two lemmas:</p>  <ol>    <li><link href="jms-00CR.xml" type="local" title="Lifting homomorphisms to the induced successor algebra">lifting <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">homomorphisms</link> to the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link></link>;</li>    <li><link href="jms-00D9.xml" type="local" title="From successor algebra homomorphisms to weak algebra homomorphisms">from <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra</link> homomorphisms to <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">weak algebra</link> <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">homomorphisms</link></link>.</li>  </ol></block>  </mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> <backmatter><contributions/> <context><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15405</anchor> <rss>jms-00CM.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00CM</addr>  <route>jms-00CM.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>1</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Successor algebras</title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>These results are attributed by <link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">Joyal and Moerdijk</link> to <link href="jeanbénabou.xml" type="local" title="Jean Bénabou">Jean Bénabou</link> and <link href="mamukajibladze.xml" type="local" title="Mamuka Jibladze">Mamuka Jibladze</link>.</p><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>4</crumb></trail> <anchor>15406</anchor> <rss>jms-00C9.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00C9</addr>  <route>jms-00C9.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Successor algebra</title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex>. A <em>successor algebra</em> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex> is defined to be a <link href="jms-00C5.xml" type="local" title="Algebra for a monad">algebra</link> <tex>X</tex> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex> together with a morphism <tex>{ X } \xrightarrow {{ s _{ X } }}{ X }</tex> in <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> called the <em>successor map</em>.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>5</crumb></trail> <anchor>15407</anchor> <rss>jms-00CA.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00CA</addr>  <route>jms-00CA.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Homomorphism of successor algebras</title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A homomorphism of <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebras</link> is a <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">monad algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ X } \xrightarrow {{ h }}{ Y }</tex> that preserves the successor operation:</p>      <center><img src="resources/15fa2278a950f050f640d89751d9b829-web.svg"/></center>  </mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>6</crumb></trail> <anchor>15408</anchor> <rss>jms-00CC.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00CC</addr>  <route>jms-00CC.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The successor restriction of a successor algebra</title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex>, and let <tex>X</tex> be an <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>. We define the <em>successor restriction</em> of <tex>X</tex> to be the <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad"><em>weak</em> algebra</link> <tex>s \cdot X  : \equiv   s _{ X } \cdot  X</tex> defined by <link href="jms-00CQ.xml" type="local" title="Restricting endofunctor algebras along endomorphisms">restricting</link> <tex>X</tex> along its successor map.</p></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>7</crumb></trail> <anchor>15409</anchor> <rss>jms-00CN.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Construction</taxon> <addr>jms-00CN</addr>  <route>jms-00CN.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>1</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>The induced <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link> on a fixed point</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter> 
<p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T} \equiv { \left ( T , \eta , \mu \right )}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex>, and let <tex>X</tex> be a <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">weak algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>. The <link href="jms-00C5.xml" type="local" title="Algebra for a monad">monad algebra</link> <tex>\bar { X }</tex> <link href="jms-00CD.xml" type="local" title="The induced monad algebra">induced by</link> <tex>X</tex> can be equipped with the structure of a <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link> by defining <tex>{ X } \xrightarrow {{ s _{ \bar { X } } }}{ X }</tex> to be the following map:</p>      <center><img src="resources/2c13b29c54b0db8c62c0e24ced11ce4b-web.svg"/></center>  </mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>8</crumb></trail> <anchor>15410</anchor> <rss>jms-00DB.rss.xml</rss>  <addr>jms-00DB</addr>  <route>jms-00DB.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Converting between <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">weak algebra</link> and <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphisms</link></title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>8</crumb> <crumb>1</crumb></trail> <anchor>15411</anchor> <rss>jms-00CR.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-00CR</addr>  <route>jms-00CR.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>1</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Lifting <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">homomorphisms</link> to the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link></title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T}   \equiv { \left ( T , \eta , \mu \right )}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> and let <tex>I</tex> be an invertible <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad"><em>weak</em> algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>; let <tex>X</tex> be an arbitrary <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link>. Then a homomorphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot X }</tex> also tracks a <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>, where <tex>\bar { I }</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> of <tex>I</tex> and <tex>s \cdot X</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link> of <tex>X</tex>.</p>      <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline>   We have <link href="jms-00CK.xml" type="local" title="Lifting homomorphisms to the induced monad algebra">already seen</link> that <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot X }</tex> tracks an <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>. It remains to show that this homomorphism preserves the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">successor operation</link>.
  <ol>    <li>      We first unfold the successor operation of the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> on <tex>I</tex>.
            <center><img src="resources/08e01bb878069433ab1603452a169e53-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    <li>      Then we use the algebra property of <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot X }</tex>.
            <center><img src="resources/8d495a60afa31fc515acc16c642b91b9-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    <li>      Then we unfold the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">restricted algebra structure</link>.
            <center><img src="resources/d4fa8dda06f6e72bdae01d93d838d825-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    <li>      Finally we the unitality of the <link href="jms-00C5.xml" type="local" title="Algebra for a monad">monad algebra</link> <tex>X</tex>.
            <center><img src="resources/545052e013d2010ed04e115d6040d267-web.svg"/></center>      </li>  </ol></block>  </mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>8</crumb> <crumb>2</crumb></trail> <anchor>15412</anchor> <rss>jms-00D9.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Lemma</taxon> <addr>jms-00D9</addr>  <route>jms-00D9.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra</link> homomorphisms to <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">weak algebra</link> <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">homomorphisms</link></title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T}   \equiv { \left ( T , \eta , \mu \right )}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> and let <tex>I</tex> be an invertible <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad"><em>weak</em> algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>; let <tex>X</tex> be an arbitrary <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link>. Then a <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex> also tracks a weak algebra homomorphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot  X }</tex>,  where <tex>\bar { I }</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> of <tex>I</tex> and <tex>s \cdot X</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link> of <tex>X</tex>.</p>      <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline>   <p>We work backwards.</p>  
  <ol>    <li>      First, we unfold the algebra structure of the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/25592c6fd1f2acc7d770d5c48083670b-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      We then use the <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> property of <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/cf12478293987bbed0635893d2e8717a-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      Next we use the <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">algebra homomorphism</link> property of <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/082898a5a8137cff0feb92ca3ea66672-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      We unfold the definition of the <link href="jms-00CD.xml" type="local" title="The induced monad algebra">induced monad algebra</link>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/720475cdd734f6e2f9b1bec2d80213a6-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      We unfold the successor map on the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/bb321a71fafde4d34d348d95da891553-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      We contract the composition of the initial (weak) algebra map with its inverse.
      
            <center><img src="resources/e07aa0172192318fc15eee56518ccae3-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
    <li>      Finally, we use the unit law of the monad <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>.
      
            <center><img src="resources/28c7265e93ee4db2d8e73b8fd06918da-web.svg"/></center>      </li>    
  </ol></block>  </mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>8</crumb> <crumb>3</crumb></trail> <anchor>15413</anchor> <rss>jms-00DA.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Corollary</taxon> <addr>jms-00DA</addr>  <route>jms-00DA.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Weak algebra <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">homomorphisms</link> and <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphisms</link> are interchangeable</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex> be a monad on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> and let <tex>I</tex> be an invertible <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad"><em>weak</em> algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>; let <tex>X</tex> be an arbitrary <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link>. Then a morphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex> in <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> tracks a weak algebra homomorphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot  X }</tex> if and only if it tracks a <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>, where <tex>\bar { I }</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> of <tex>I</tex> and <tex>s \cdot X</tex> is the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link> of <tex>X</tex>.</p>      <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline>   <p>This follows from the following two lemmas:</p>  <ol>    <li><link href="jms-00CR.xml" type="local" title="Lifting homomorphisms to the induced successor algebra">lifting <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">homomorphisms</link> to the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link></link>;</li>    <li><link href="jms-00D9.xml" type="local" title="From successor algebra homomorphisms to weak algebra homomorphisms">from <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra</link> homomorphisms to <link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">weak algebra</link> <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">homomorphisms</link></link>.</li>  </ol></block>  </mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="true" show-heading="true" show-metadata="false" toc="true" root="false"><frontmatter><trail><crumb>9</crumb></trail> <anchor>15414</anchor> <rss>jms-00D8.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Theorem</taxon> <addr>jms-00D8</addr>  <route>jms-00D8.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>11</month> <day>5</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>From initial <link href="jms-00CD.xml" type="local" title="The induced monad algebra">weak algebras</link> to initial <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebras</link></title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>I</tex> be the initial weak algebra for a monad <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex> on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex>. Then the <link href="jms-00CN.xml" type="local" title="The induced successor algebra on a fixed point">induced successor algebra</link> <tex>\bar { I }</tex> is the <em>initial</em> <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebra</link> for <tex>\mathbb {T}</tex>.</p>      <block open="open"><headline><strong>Proof</strong>.</headline>   <p>Let <tex>X</tex> be a successor algebra; <link href="jms-00CR.xml" type="local" title="Lifting homomorphisms to the induced successor algebra">we have shown</link> that weak algebra homomorphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ \iota }}{ s \cdot X }</tex> from <tex>I</tex> to the <link href="jms-00CC.xml" type="local" title="The successor restriction of a successor algebra">successor restriction</link> of <tex>X</tex> also tracks a successor algebra homomorphism <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ \iota }}{ X }</tex>. To see that this homomorphism is <em>unique</em>, fix any <link href="jms-00CA.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of successor algebras">successor algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ \bar { I } } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ X }</tex>; we <link href="jms-00D9.xml" type="local" title="From successor algebra homomorphisms to weak algebra homomorphisms">have also shown</link> that such a homomorphism also tracks a (<link href="jms-00C8.xml" type="local" title="Weak algebra for a monad">weak algebra</link>) homomorphism <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ j }}{ s \cdot X }</tex>. But <tex>{ I } \xrightarrow {{ \iota }}{ s \cdot X }</tex> is the such weak algebra homomorphism, so we have <tex>\iota  = j</tex>.</p></block>  </mainmatter> </tree></mainmatter> </tree></context> <related><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15415</anchor> <rss>jms-00C7.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00C7</addr>  <route>jms-00C7.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Homomorphism of algebras</title> </frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>Let <tex>F</tex> be an endofunctor on a category <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> and let <tex>X , Y</tex> be a pair of <link href="jms-00C6.xml" type="local" title="Algebra for an endofunctor">algebras for <tex>F</tex></link>; a <em>homomorphism</em> of algebras from <tex>X</tex> to <tex>Y</tex> is given by a morphism <tex>{ X } \xrightarrow {{ h }}{ Y }</tex> in <tex>\mathcal {C}</tex> that preserves the algebra structure in the following sense:</p>      <center><img src="resources/9f8aee5b68f404fda23e30bed2a3c248-web.svg"/></center>  </mainmatter> </tree><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15416</anchor> <rss>jms-00CA.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Definition</taxon> <addr>jms-00CA</addr>  <route>jms-00CA.xml</route> <date><year>2023</year> <month>10</month> <day>30</day></date> <authors><author><link href="jonmsterling.xml" type="local">Jon Sterling</link></author> </authors> <title>Homomorphism of successor algebras</title> <meta name="source"><link href="joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml" type="local" title="Algebraic set theory">[joyal-moerdijk-1995]</link></meta></frontmatter> <mainmatter><p>A homomorphism of <link href="jms-00C9.xml" type="local" title="Successor algebra">successor algebras</link> is a <link href="jms-00C7.xml" type="local" title="Homomorphism of algebras">monad algebra homomorphism</link> <tex>{ X } \xrightarrow {{ h }}{ Y }</tex> that preserves the successor operation:</p>      <center><img src="resources/15fa2278a950f050f640d89751d9b829-web.svg"/></center>  </mainmatter> </tree></related> <backlinks/> <references><tree expanded="false" show-heading="true" show-metadata="true" toc="false" root="false"><frontmatter> <anchor>15417</anchor> <rss>joyal-moerdijk-1995.rss.xml</rss> <taxon>Reference</taxon> <addr>joyal-moerdijk-1995</addr>  <route>joyal-moerdijk-1995.xml</route> <date><year>1995</year>  </date> <authors><author><link href="andréjoyal.xml" type="local">André Joyal</link></author><author><link href="iekemoerdijk.xml" type="local">Ieke Moerdijk</link></author> <